      <div class="section" data-name="introduction">
        <div class="title">Introduction</div>
        <div class="text">
          <p>Welcome to the Mobatec Modeller help file. This file is designed to help any user (from beginners to modelling experts) and it contains information and examples on all features of the software.</p>
          <p>If you can't find information you are looking for or need assistance please feel free to e-mail us on <a href="mailto:help@mobatec.nl">help@mobatec.nl</a></p>
        </div>
      </div><!--Section END-->
      <div class="section" data-name="about-the-software">
        <div class="title">About the software</div>
        <div class="text">
          <p>Mobatec Modeller is a process modelling and simulation software that is designed to make dynamic or steady state process models.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom:0px;">It is a 32-bit program with the following system requirements:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Operating system:</b> Windows 7 or higher</li>
            <li><b>Processor:</b> 1 gigahertz (GHz) or faster</li>
            <li><b>RAM:</b> 2GB or more</li>
            <li><b>Hard Disk Space:</b> 500MB</li>
            <li><b>Graphics Card:</b> DirectX 9 or later</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Mobatec Modeller is also cloud ready, so it can run inside any web browser without needing to install anything on your machine. If you are interested in this feature please contact us on <a href="mailto:cloud@mobatec.nl">cloud@mobatec.nl</a></p>
          <p>Simple models don't take a lot of computational power but if your models are big (have a lot of equations) we recommend that you have higher processing power and more processor cores on your machine so your models solve faster.</p>
        </div>
      </div><!--Section END-->
